<paragraph id="AC328032CE66BA572D57369ABE2D0A12" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D2EB756CFA48C6B6BDEC7FC1882583F6" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">The specific epithet formed from the Latin adjective latilobus referring to penis guide which is wide at basal half, sharply narrowed and forming a distinct gap in middle.</paragraph>
